==English==
{{wikipediapar|Macaca (slur)}}
===Etymology===
From French ''[[macaque]]'' < Portuguese ''[[macaco]]'' (monkey) < Bantu.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
#{{slang}} An [[embarrassment]] or [[embarrassing]] [[moment]].
#:''"Well I guess this is my '''macaca''' payback."'' —[[James H. Webb]]<ref>[http://www.c-span.org/VideoArchives.asp?z1=&PopupMenu_Name=Politics/Elections&CatCodePairs=Issue,PE;], James H. Webb; prefacing his answer to a question about his former anti-female statements. ''[[C-SPAN]]'' (video recording 59:04/1:11:26) Monday, [[September 18]], [[2006]] ([[RealPlayer]] format).  The most contemporary usage of the word, made in the presence of many professional writers.</ref>
#{{italbrac|racial slur}} A [[derogatory]] [[epithet]] for dark-skinned people who appear to be of Middle-Eastern descent.
#{{archaic}} {{slang}} {{italbrac|racial slur}} A dismissive epithet used by French-speaking colonials in Central Africa to refer to a native of the Congo or persons of native Congo ethnicity.

